    • Constructor Detail

      • CommonProperties

        public CommonProperties()
        Constructs an empty set of common properties, with most values being set to null, 0, or empty (depending on the type of the property). Usually this constructor is used if this configuration POJO is populated in an automated fashion (e.g. injection). If you need to build them manually (possibly with defaults), use or create a properties builder.

        You can change the defaults with the setters.

        See Also:
        MapBasedCommonPropsBuilder.buildDefault(), MapBasedCommonPropsBuilder.build(java.util.Map)

      • CommonProperties

      • setProcessors

        public final void setProcessors(String processors)
        Set the processor chain to instantiate.

        Provide the processor chain as a comma separated list of fully qualified class names. Classes must implement the Processor interface. The order of the processors matter, the chain will be built from left to right.

        Parameters:
        processors - The date format string to use

      • setAdditionalProperties

        public final void setAdditionalProperties(Map<String,String> additionalProperties)
        Any additional properties which have not been parsed, and for which no getter/setter exists, but are to be stored in this object nevertheless.

        This property is commonly used to preserve original properties from upstream components that are to be passed on to downstream components unchanged. This properties set may or may not include properties that have been extracted from the map, and been made available through this POJO.

        Note that these additional properties may be null or empty, even in a fully populated POJO where other properties commonly have values assigned to.

        Parameters:
        additionalProperties - The additional properties to store
